s%20are%20expected%20to%20start%20rebounding%20as%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ft.com%2Fcontent%2F2b9c7e75-74a0-4410-b7b3-8bba9dd7fdbc%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehome%20heating%20policy%3C%2Fa%3E%20becomes%20better%20understood%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnbc.com%2F2024%2F04%2F11%2Feuropean-central-bank-holds-interest-rates-hints-at-cut-ahead.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEuropean%20Central%20Bank%20signals%3C%2Fa%3E%20it%20will%20soon%20cut%20interest%20rates%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.imf.org%2Fen%2FBlogs%2FArticles%2F2023%2F11%2F07%2Feuropes-wage-rises-are-aiding-recovery-but-economies-face-risks%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewages%20rise%20faster%20than%20prices%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BThe%20German%20market%20for%20house%20prices%20is%20close%20to%20bottoming%20out%2C%20and%20the%20same%20probably%20holds%20for%20building%20permits%20and%20residential%20construction%2C%26quot%3B%20Schmieding%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrance%20similarly%20saw%20housing%20costs%20steadily%20climb%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20but%2C%20like%20Germany%2C%20has%20seen%20its%20prices%20come%20down%20amid%20high%20interest%20rates.%20Schmieding%20also%20expects%20home%20prices%20and%20rents%20to%20tick%20back%20up%20later%20this%20year%20in%20France%20as%20long%20as%20interest%20rates%20come%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20country%20is%20still%20facing%20housing%20affordability%20issues%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0a%20situation%20one%20prominent%20charity%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2024%2F03%2F17%2Frealestate%2Fparis-france-housing-costs.html%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520Fondation%2520Abb%25C3%25A9%2520Pierre%252C%2520an%2Cfrom%25202%2520million%2520in%25202017.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecently%20called%20%26quot%3Ba%20social%20bomb%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20%C2%A0%E2%80%94%20with%20rising%20homelessness%20and%20a%20growing%20waitlist%20for%20social%20housing.%20The%20Paris%20Olymp