tters.html%5C%22%3Eoutlet%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20career%20consultant%20explained%20that%20%26quot%3Bemployers%20have%20been%20suspecting%20that%20job%20seekers%20have%20been%20using%20ChatGPT%20after%20%26quot%3Bgetting%20hundreds%20of%20the%20exact%20same%20cover%20letters%20word%20for%20word%2C%26quot%3B%20or%20answers%20to%20job%20application%20questions%20that%20are%20the%20same.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20as%20per%20%3Cem%3ECNBC%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20a%20Canva%20survey%20revealed%2045%25%20of%20job%20seekers%20have%20used%20AI%20to%20build%2C%20update%20or%20improve%20their%20resume.%20And%20it%20appears%20that%20gen%20Z%20is%20leaning%20the%20most%20on%20artificial%20intelligence%2C%20according%20to%20a%20Grammarly%20survey.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAlso%20read%20%7C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fwomen-only-exhibit-in-australian-museum-to-become-toilet-to-keep-men-out-5623094%5C%22%3EWomen-Only%20Exhibit%20In%20Australian%20Museum%20To%20Become%20Toilet%20To%20Keep%20Men%20Out%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMs%20Davis%20said%20that%20while%20we%20should%20definitely%20%26quot%3Bembrace%20technology%20and%20AI%2C%26quot%3B%20copying%20answers%20from%20ChatGPT%20can%20hurt%20your%20chances%20of%20getting%20a%20job.%20She%20also%20shared%20a%20recent%20incident%20with%20a%20recruiter%20hiring%20for%20a%20brand%20marketing%20position.%20She%20said%20that%20the%20candidates%20were%20asked%20a%20question%20in%20the%20job%20application%20about%20their%20favourite%20fitness-related%20product%20launches%20in%20the%20past%20year.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20said%20they%20got%20about%20100%20identical%20responses%20of%20'my%20favourite%20campaign%20launch%20was%20Peloton'%20and%20the%20employer%20was%20like%20'ultimately%20that%20was%20ChatGPT%2C%20but%20then%20also%20equally%20Peloton%20was%20released%20like%20four%20or%20five%20years%20ago'%2C%26quot%3B%20Ms%20Dav