ent%20that%20today's%20older%20Gen%20Xers%20are%20ready%20to%20retire%2C%20their%20Social%20Security%20benefits%20could%20start%20to%20shrink.%20That%20could%20be%20a%20real%20problem%20for%20a%20generation%20that%20was%20already%20suffering%20in%20silence.%20Gen%20Xers%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fguides.loc.gov%2Fconsumer-research%2Fmarket-segments%2Fgenerations%23%3A~%3Atext%3DGeneration%2520X%252C%2520defined%2520by%2520the%2Cdebuted%2520in%2520their%2520formative%2520years.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eborn%20from%201965%20to%201980%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20have%20been%20deemed%20the%20country's%20%26quot%3Bneglected%20middle%20child%26quot%3B%20by%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fshort-reads%2F2014%2F06%2F05%2Fgeneration-x-americas-neglected-middle-child%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPew%20Research%20Center%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2239e6516e-7678-418c-ab51-af3cb3c8ef26%5C%22%3EGen%20X%20is%20deeper%20in%20debt%20and%20more%20worried%20about%20finances%20than%20other%20generations%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20might%20be%20able%20to%20chalk%20up%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EGen%20X's%20invisibility%20to%20the%20fact%20that%2C%20per%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fguides.loc.gov%2Fconsumer-research%2Fmarket-segments%2Fgenerations%23%3A~%3Atext%3DGeneration%2520X%252C%2520defined%2520by%2520the%2Cdebuted%2520in%2520their%2520formative%2520years.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELibrary%20of%20Congress%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20they're%20the%20smallest%20generation%20population-wise.%20Their%20plights%20have%20been%20dwarfed%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fshort-reads%2F2020%2F04%2F28%2Fmillennials-overtake-baby-boomers-as-americas-largest-generation%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emillennials%3C%2Fa%3E'%20massive%20ranks%20and%20prominent%20woes%2C%20and%20the%20huge%20peak%20boomer%20population%20that's%20about%20to%20settle%20into%20retirement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-x-forgotten-they-like-it-that-way-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGen%20X%3C%2Fa%3Eers%20have%20already%20been%20quietly%20dealing%20with%20some%20financial%20insecurity.%20In%20July%202023%2C%20Business%20Insider%20%E2%80%94%20in%20partnership%20with%20YouGov%20%E2%80%94%20surveyed%20over%201%2C800%20Americans%20spanning%20five%20generations%2C%20asking%20about%20work%2C%20money%2C%20and%20relationships.%20And%20among%20the%20different%20generations%2C%20Gen%20Xers%20were%20the%20most%20likely%20to%20report%20that%20they%20were%20feeling%20financially%20insecure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2F8VDCB%2F2%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22How%20financially%20secure%20generations%20feel%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22342%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.experian.com%2Fblogs%2Fask-experian%2Fresearch%2Fconsumer-debt-study%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EExperian%3C%2Fa%3E%20consumer%20data%20shows%20that%20the%20total%20average%20debt%20for%20Gen%20X%20has%20been%20near%20or%20over%20%24150%2C000%20in%20the%20third%20quarters%20of%202021%20to%202023%2C%20higher%20than%20both%20their%20younger%20and%20older%20counterparts.%20The%20generation%20also%20had%20over%20%249%2C000%20in%20average%20credit%20card%20debt%2C%20based%20on%20data%20from%20the%20third%20quarter%20of%202023%2C%20which%20was%20not%20only%20a%20rise%20from%20their%20average%20credit%20card%20debt%20a%20year%20prior%20but%20far%20above%20the%20national%20average%20of%20%246%2C501%20or%20the%20average%20for%20other%20generations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGeneration%20X%20is%20the%20generation%20most%20likely%20to%20have%20the%20richest%20credit%20mix%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Experian%20post%20stated.%20%26quot%3BThat%20may%20sound%20like%20a%20flex%2C%20but%20in%20practical%20terms%20it%20means%20these%20consumers%20are%20likely%20to%20have%20multiple%20monthly%20payments%20to%20service%E2%80%94think%20student%20loan%2C%20mortgage%2C%20credit%20card%20and%20car%20payments.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20not%20to%20say%20other%20generations%20aren't%20encountering%20similar%20challenges.%20According%20to%20a%20new%20TransUnion%20study%20based%20on%20credit%20bureau%20data%20and%20a%20December%202023%20survey%20of%20just%20over%201%2C200%20Gen%20Z%20and%20millennial%20consumers%2C%20the%20youngest%20generation%20is%20disproportionately%20struggling%20to%20balance%20a%20range%20of%20credit%20products%20amid%20high%20inflation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpecifically%2C%20Gen%20Zers%20are%20seeing%20higher%20levels%20of%20delinquency%20on%20products%20like%20credit%20cards%20and%20auto%20loans%20compared%20to%20millennials%2010%20years%20earlier%2C%20with%2075%25%20of%20Gen%20Z%20respondents%20saying%20the%20pandemic%20negatively%20influenced%20their%20finances.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGen%20Z%20consumers%20have%20seen%20their%20finances%20significantly%20impacted%20by%20the%20pandemic%20and%20its%20aftermath%2C%20even%20more%20so%20than%20the%20challenges%20faced%20by%20Millennials%20as%20a%20result%20of%20the%20Global%20Financial%20Crisis%2C%26quot%3B%20Michele%20Raneri%2C%20vice%20president%20and%20head%20of%20US%20research%20and%20consulting%20at%20TransUnion%2C%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aarp.org%2Fresearch%2Ftopics%2Feconomics%2Finfo-2023%2Ffinancial-security-trends-survey.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAARP%20Financial%20Security%20Trends%20Survey%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20January%20showed%20that%20around%20a%20third%20of%20those%20aged%2050%20and%20over%20%E2%80%94%20that%20is%2C%20the%20results%20include%20part%20of%20Gen%20X%20%E2%80%94%2