tes%20and%20two%20Union%20Territories%20that%20went%20to%20polls%2C%20only%20three%20-%20Chhattisgarh%2C%20Goa%2C%20and%20Karnataka%20-%20recorded%20an%20increase%20in%20turnout%20compared%20to%202019.%20Assam%2C%20Chhattisgarh%2C%20Dadra%20%26amp%3B%20Nagar%20Haveli%2C%20Daman%20%26amp%3B%20Diu%2C%20Goa%2C%20Karnataka%2C%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20and%20West%20Bengal%20have%20recorded%20higher%20turnouts%20than%20the%20overall%20average.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ETrends%20In%20Hindi%20Heartland%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Hindi%20heartland%20states%20of%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20(-2.5%20percentage%20points%2C%20or%20p.p.)%2C%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20(-0.6%20p.p.)%2C%20and%20Bihar%20(-3.1%20p.p.)%20appear%20to%20be%20dragging%20down%20the%20overall%20turnout.%20Although%20Madhya%20Pradesh's%20numbers%20look%20better%20in%20this%20phase%2C%20these%20states%20have%20consistently%20recorded%20lower%20turnout%20in%20all%20phases.%20The%20unexpected%20inclusion%20in%20this%20group%2C%20joining%20hands%20with%20the%20Hindi%20heartland%20states%20to%20lower%20the%20overall%20turnout%2C%20are%20the%20industrialised%20states%20of%20Gujarat%20and%20Maharashtra.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20scorching%20heat%2C%20lack%20of%20enthusiasm%20among%20both%20ruling%20party%20and%20opposition%20camps%2C%20voter%20fatigue%20and%20urban%20apathy%20are%20some%20of%20the%20reasons%20for%20a%20lower%20turnout%2C%20each%20state%20has%20a%20different%20story%20to%20tell.%3Cbr%3E%5CnAssam%20has%20recorded%20brisk%20voting%2C%20though%20there%20is%20a%20decline%20of%203.4%25%2C%20largely%20due%20to%20the%20higher%20base.%20Similarly%2C%20West%20Bengal%20has%20consistently%20recorded%20high%20voting%20of%20over%2075%25%20in%20all%20three%20phases%2C%20and%20the%20decline%20could%20be%20largely%20attributed%20to%20the%20base%20effect%20here%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBihar%20continues%20to%20record%20a%20lower%20turnout%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20among%20the%20lowest%20in%20all%20three%20phases.%20Janata%20Dal%20(United)%20(JD-U)%20candidates%20were%20in%20the%20fray%20in%20three%20of%20the%20five%20seats.%20It%20seems%20Nitish%20Kumar's%20constant%20flip-flops%20have%20caused%20discontent%20among%20a%20section%20of%20his%20core%20voters.%20It%20may%20also%20be%20the%20case%20that%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20voters%20are%20not%20coming%20out%20wholeheartedly%20to%20support%20JDU%20candidates.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENotably%2C%20both%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20and%20Bihar%20also%20record%20lower%20turnouts%20in%20state%20polls%20and%20migration%20is%20one%20of%20the%20reasons%20for%20the%20same.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EGujarat's%20Lower%20Numbers%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Gujarat%2C%20the%20home%20turf%20of%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20and%20the%20Union%20Home%20Minister%2C%20the%20turnout%20was%20lower%20than%20in%202019%20by%203.1%20p.p.%20Gujarat%20has%20a%20history%20of%20lower%20turnouts%20in%20state%20elections%20of%202017%20and%202022.%20Here%2C%20the%20near-complete%20demolition%20of%20the%20Congress%20party's%20organisational%20structure%20may%20have%20led%20to%20demotivation%20among%20opposition%20supporters%2C%20resulting%20in%20a%20lower%20turnout.%20Additionally%2C%20some%20opposition%20voters%20may%20not%20wish%20to%20vote%20against%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20and%20the%20Home%20Minister%2C%20both%20local%20heroes%20who%20are%20leading%20the%20nation%20in%20the%20name%20of%20Gujarati%20pride.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20the%20decline%20is%20marginal%20and%20can%20be%20ignored.%20However%2C%20in%20Maharashtra%2C%20the%20decline%20of%202.5%20p.p.%20is%20intriguing.%20Baramati%2C%20which%20is%20facing%20a%20Pawar%20versus%20Pawar%20battle%2C%20recorded%20one%20of%20the%20lowest%20turnouts%20across%20the%2093%20seats%2C%20at%20only%2056.1%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20INDIA%20bloc%20has%20high%20hopes%20for%20Maharashtra%20as%20they%20believe%20Uddhav%20Thackeray%20and%20Sharad%20Pawar%20could%20enjoy%20a%20sympathy%20factor%20after%20the%20alleged%20'Operation%20Lotus'%20against%20their%20parties.%20However%2C%20the%20numbers%20are%20not%20encouraging%2C%20indicating%20a%20lack%20of%20enthusiasm%20and%20apathy.%20Parties%20changing%20partners%2C%20dishonouring%20mandates%2C%20and%20the%20constant%20flip-flops%20of%20leaders%20may%20have%20kept%20some%20people%20out%20of%20the%20political%20process.%20Also%2C%20there%20is%20confusion%20among%20a%20section%20of%20voters%20regarding%20future%20realignments.%20Will%20Uddhav%20come%20back%20to%20the%20National%20Democratic%20Alliance%20(NDA)%3F%20Will%20Ajit%20Pawar%20go%20back%20to%20the%20Maha%20Vikas%20Aghadi%20(MVA)%20or%20the%20INDIA%20bloc%3F%20All%20these%20possibilities%20cannot%20be%20ruled%20out%20in%20a%20state%20that%20has%20seen%20it%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat's%20Keeping%20UP%20Voters%20Away%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUttar%20Pradesh%20continues%20to%20record%20a%20lower%20turnout%2C%20among%20the%20lowest%20in%20all%20three%20phases.%20A%20perceived%20done%20deal%20might%20be%20keeping%20opposition%20voters%20out%2C%20or%20complacency%20might%20be%20creeping%20in%20among%20BJP%20supporters%2Fcadre.%20Are%20Bahujan%20Samaj%20Party%20(BSP)%20supporters%20not%20coming%20out%20to%20vote%2C%20as%20Mayawati%20contesting%20alone%20has%20no%20chance%3F%20Is%20the%20alliance%20with%20the%20Rashtriya%20Lok%20Dal%20(RLD)%20not%20working%20on%20the%20ground%3F%20The%20relative%20turnout%20of%20community%20groups%20is%20also%20important%20in%20the%20state.%20Both%20BJP%20and%20Congress%20have%20put%20up%2020-25%25%20candidates%20who%20were%20earlier%20in%20other%20parties.%20Are%20party%20workers%20not%20wholeheartedly%20working%20for%20these%20newbies%3F%20Turnout%20is%20a%20complex%20phenomenon%20to%20decipher.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20analysts%20have%20argued%20that%20since%20the%20voter%20base%20has%20increased%20by%20around%208%20crore%2C%20a%20lower%20turnout%20also%20results%20in%20a%20higher%20number%20of%20votes%20cast%20(in%20absolute%20terms).%20They%20also%20cite%20a%20high%20base%20effect%2C%20with%20a%20high%20turnout%20in%202019%20given%20the%20strong%20nationalism%20fervour%20back%20then.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20it's%20also%20intriguing%20that%20states%20that%20witnessed%20turnouts%20of%2070-75%25%20in%20assembly%20polls%20in%20December%202023%20are%20recording%20a%20decline%20of%205-10%20p.p.%20in%20Lok%20Sabha%20polls.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Amitabh%20Tiwari%20is%20a%20political%20strategist%20and%20commentator.%20In%20his%20earlier%20avatar%2C%20he%20was%20a%20corporate%20and%20investment%20banker)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1715238780000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-05%2Fa6hbd04k_voting_640x480_07_May_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Flok-sabha-polls-low-turnout-continues-in-phase-3-how-states-have-performed-5623409%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Among%20the%2010%20states%20and%20two%20Union%20Territories%20that%20went%20to%20polls%2C%20only%20three%20-%20Chhattisgarh%2C%20Goa%2C%20and%20Karnataka%20-%20recorded%20an%20increase%20in%20turnout%20compared%20to%202019.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Flok-sabha-polls-low-turnout-continues-in-phase-3-how-states-have-performed-5623409%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'It%20was%20a%20beautiful%20journey'%3A'%20Aashish%20quits%20Anupamaa%20after%20almost%204%20yrs%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1715238689000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-109972717%2Cimgsize-1353326.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Ftv%2Fnews%2Fhindi%2Ftoshu-aka-aashish-mehrotra-quits-