dians%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EAustralia%20has%20made%20it%C2%A0tougher%C2%A0for%20international%20students%20to%20get%20visas.%20It%20has%20increased%20the%C2%A0amount%20of%C2%A0money%20a%20student%20must%20have%20as%20savings%20to%C2%A0enter%20the%20country.%20The%20required%20amount%20will%20now%20be%2075%25%20of%20the%20national%20minimum%20wage.%20Effective%20May%2010%2C%202024%2C%20students%C2%A0will%20have%20to%C2%A0show%20they%20have%20at%20least%20A%2429%2C710%20(%E2%82%B916%2C29%2C964)%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fimmi.homeaffairs.gov.au%2Fnews-media%2Farchive%2Farticle%3FitemId%3D1196%C2%A0%5C%22%3Equalify%20for%20a%20visa%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20change%C2%A0is%20meant%C2%A0to%20ensure%20students%20can%20afford%20basic%20living%20expenses%20while%20studying%20in%20Australia%2C%20considering%20they%20may%20not%20be%20in%20class%20for%2025%25%20of%20the%20year%20and%20work%20during%20that%20time.%20Meeting%20this%20requirement%20will%20help%20students%20plan%20their%20future%20better.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%C2%A0is%20the%20second%20time%C2%A0in%20seven%20months%C2%A0the%20amount%20of%20savings%20has%20been%20increased%2C%20following%20a%20previous%20hike%20to%20A%2424%2C505%20(%E2%82%B913%2C44%2C405)%20from%20A%2421%2C041%20(%E2%82%B911%2C54%2C361)%20in%20October.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20is%20tightening%20visa%20rules%20after%20reports%20of%C2%A0lots%20of%C2%A0people%20moving%20to%20Australia%20since%C2%A0the%20COVID-19%20restrictions%20were%20lifted%C2%A0in%202022.%C2%A0This%C2%A0has%20caused%20problems%2C%20like%20a%20shortage%20of%20rental%20homes.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20March%2C%20the%20government%20also%20raised%20English%20language%20requirements%20for%20student%20visas%20and%20has%C2%A0been%20implementing%C2%A0policies%20to%20prevent%20students%20from%20extending%20their%20stay%20through%20various%20loopholes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Australia%20Visa%20News%2C%20the%20number%20of%20temporary%20student%20visas%20granted%20in%20the%20country%20reached%20a%20record%20high%20of%206%2C54%2C870%20in%20July%202023%2C%C2%A0marking%C2%A0a%20significant%20increase%20from%20the%20previous%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Australian%20government%20has%20implemented%20other%20measures%20to%20support%20international%20students%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E1.%20The%20Australian%20government%20replaced%20the%20Genuine%20Temporary%20Entrant%20(GTE)%20requirement%20with%20a%20Genuine%20Student%20(GS)%20requirement%20to%C2%A0make%20sure%20students%20are%20genuinely%20coming%20to%C2%A0study%2C%C2%A0and%C2%A0not%20just%20to%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E2.%20Post-Study%20Work%20Rights%20(PSWR)%20were%20extended%20by%20up%20to%20two%20years%20from%20July%201%2C%202023%2C%20allowing%20students%20to%20find%20employment%20related%20to%20their%20field%20of%20study.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E3.%20A%20minimum%C2%A0total%C2%A0score%20of%205.5%C2%A0is%20required%C2%A0for%20international%20students%20enrolling%20in%20universities%20and%20programs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E4.%C2%A0Work%20hours%20during%20study%20terms%20and%20semesters%20were%20limited%20to%2048%20hours%20per%20fortnight%20from%20July%201%2C%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E5.%C2%A0The%20Skilled-Recognised%20Graduate%20visa%2C%20which%20previously%20allowed%20recent%20engineering%20graduates%20to%20stay%2C%20work%2C%20or%20study%20in%20Australia%20for%20up%20to%2018%20months%2C%20now%20has%20a%20limit%20on%20it%20from%20December%2022%2C%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E6.%20International%20students%C2%A0are%20no%20longer%20allowed%20to%C2%A0enrol%20in%20two%20courses%20simultaneously%20within%20the%20first%20six%20months%20of%20their%20principal%20course%2C%20effective%C2%A0from%C2%A0September%208%2C%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1715234220000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2020-07%2Ft8d2vrek_australia-generic-sydney-generic-sydney-opera-house-pixabay_625x300_