5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EColon%20cancer%20cases%20have%20more%20than%20doubled%20in%20people%20in%20their%20teens%20and%2020s%2C%20according%20to%20CDC%20data.%3Cp%3Eljubaphoto%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ECancer%20rates%20in%20people%20under%2045%20have%20surged%20over%20the%20past%20two%20decades%2C%20researchers%20found.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EDiagnoses%20are%20increasing%20most%20rapidly%20in%20teens%20and%20people%20in%20their%20early%2020s.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EFactors%20such%20as%20genetics%2C%20alcohol%20use%2C%20diet%2C%20and%20physical%20activity%20may%20influence%20cancer%20risk.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ENew%20evidence%20shows%20how%20sharply%20colon%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcancer-young-rates-colorectal-breast-stomach-colon-treatment-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecancer%20rates%20are%20skyrocketing%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20people%20younger%20than%2045.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20team%20of%20researchers%20led%20by%20Dr.%20Islam%20Mohamed%2C%20a%20physician%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Missouri-Kansas%20City%2C%20analyzed%20CDC%20data%20on%20colon%20cancer%20incidence%20in%20Americans%20aged%2010%20to%2044%20over%20two%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20found%20that%20cases%20have%20more%20than%20tripled%20in%20teenagers%20and%20more%20than%20doubled%20for%20people%20in%20their%20early%2020s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20biggest%20jump%20in%20cancer%20diagnoses%20was%20in%20younger%20people%2C%20the%20surge%20in%20cancer%20rates%20was%20significant%20across%20all%20age%20groups%20under%2045%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3ELate%2020s%20to%20early%2030s%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20rate%20of%20people%20diagnosed%20with%20colon%20cancer%20in%20this%20age%20range%20increased%20about%2070%25%20from%201999%20to%202020.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3ELate%2030s%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EFor%20this%20age%20group%2C%20the%20rate%20increased%2058%25%20in%20the%20same%20time%20period.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EEarly%2040s%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThis%20demographic%20had%20the%20highest%20overall%20rate.%20Cancer%20cases%20increased%20by%2045%25%20for%20people%20in%20their%20early%2040s%20from%201999%20to%202020.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20will%20be%20presented%20at%20Digestive%20Disease%20Week%2C%20a%20meeting%20for%20professionals%20in%20gastroenterology%20and%20related%20fields%2C%20from%20May%2018%20to%2021%20in%20Washington%2C%20D.C.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20findings%20suggest%20a%20need%20for%20better%20awareness%2C%20treatment%2C%20and%20prevention%20options%20for%20younger%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BColorectal%20cancer%20is%20no%20longer%20considered%20just%20a%20disease%20of%20the%20elderly%20population%2C%26quot%3B%20Mohamed%20said%20in%20a%20press%20release.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20important%20that%20the%20public%20is%20aware%20of%20signs%20and%20symptoms%20of%20colorectal%20cancer.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2291e8cd8d-a50b-416d-a943-c3fce747e1b9%5C%22%3EColon%20cancer%20signs%20to%20look%20out%20for%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERegular%20testing%20can%20be%20particularly%20important%20for%20colon%20cancer%20because%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcolon-cancer-red-flag-signs-symptoms-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esymptoms%3C%2Fa%3E%20can%20be%20hard%20to%20recognize%20until%20more%20advanced%20stages%20of%20the%20disease.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20common%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcolorectal-cancer-high-mortality-young-people-signs-symptoms-disease-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eearly%20warning%20signs%20of%20colon%20cancer%3C%2Fa%3E%20include%20abdominal%20pain%2C%20rectal%20bleeding%2C%20anemia%20(iron%20deficiency)%2C%20and%20changes%20to%20bathroom%20habits%20(like%20diarrhea%20or%20constipation)%2C%20according%20to%20Mohamed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20increase%20is%20striking%2C%20overall%20numbers%20of%20colon%20cancer%20diagnoses%20in%20young%20people%20are%20still%20low.%20In%202020%2C%20there%20were%201.3%20cases%20per%20100%2C000%20teenagers%20and%202%20cases%20per%20100%2C000%20people%20in%20their%20early%2020s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20colonoscopy%20screening%20is%20only%20recommended%20for%20people%20older%20than%2045%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cdc.gov%2Fcancer%2Fcolorectal%2Fbasic_info%2Fscreening%2Ftests.htm%23%3A~%3Atext%3DA%2520colonoscopy%2520is%2520one%2520of%2Cbe%2520screened%2520for%2520colorectal%2520cancer.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECDC%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2209b4d961-f087-47ad-9831-5d08a68ffc71%5C%22%3EStrategies%20to%20prevent%20colon%20cancer%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20potentially%20preventable%20risk%20factor%20behind%20the%20rising%20cancer%20rates%20is%20diet%2C%20as%20some%20evidence%20suggests%20that%20consuming%20more%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprocessed-food-cancer-bmj-2018-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprocessed%20foods%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20added%20sugar%20are%20linked%20to%20greater%20odds%20of%20developing%20cancer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStrategies%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcolon-cancer-risks-young-people-reduce-diet-alcohol-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereduce%20your%20risk%20of%20colon%20cancer%3C%2Fa%3E%20include%20eating%20enough%20fiber%20and%20avoiding%20tobacco%20and%20alcohol.%20Regular%20exercise%20has%20also%20been%20linked%20to%20a%20lower%20risk%20of%20multiple%20types%20of%20cancer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20colon%20cancer%20risk%20can%20also%20be%20genetic.%20Ongoing%20research%20is%20investigating%20whether%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcolon-cancer-diagnosis-young-people-gut-bacteria-microbiome-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egut%20microbiome%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20bacteria%20in%20the%20digestive%20system%